\sqrt{3x}
\sqrt 3(x) = x + \sqrt 3
\begin{align} \sqrt 3(x) = x + \sqrt 3 & \iff (\sqrt 3 - 1)x = \sqrt 3 \\ \\ &\iff x = \dfrac {\sqrt 3}{\sqrt 3 - 1} \\ \\ &\iff x = \frac{\sqrt 3}{\sqrt 3 - 1} \cdot \frac{\sqrt 3 + 1}{\sqrt 3 + 1} = \dfrac{3 +\sqrt 3}{3 - 1} = \dfrac 32 + \dfrac {\sqrt 3}2\end{align}
