\sqrt{3x}=x+\sqrt{3}
3x=x^2+2x\sqrt{3}+3
x^2+(2\sqrt{3}-3)x+3=0
D=(2\sqrt{3}-3)^2-4 \times 1 \times 3=12-12\sqrt{3}+9-12=9-12\sqrt{3}<0
x^2 + (2\sqrt{3} - 3)x + 3 = 0
x = 1.5 -\sqrt{3} \pm \sqrt{(1.5-\sqrt{3})^2 - 3}
